<!DOCTYPE html>
<!--
  ink-board dashboard template — 296×128 px, tri-color (black/white/red)

  DESIGN RULES:
  - Viewport is fixed at 296×128 px (set by the renderer).
  - Use ONLY these colors: #000000 (black), #ffffff (white), #ff0000 (red).
    Any other color will be quantized to the nearest tri-color equivalent
    by the firmware's classifyColor() function. Grays → black, pinks → red.
  - No external resources (no web fonts, no remote images) — the renderer
    runs offline and does not load external URLs.
  - For custom fonts, embed them as base64 @font-face declarations or use
    safe system fonts: monospace, sans-serif, serif.
  - Preview in your browser: open this file and inject a mock data object
    via the browser console, or use a local HTTP server with ?mock=1.

  TEMPLATE VARIABLES:
  The EJS template receives a `data` object whose keys match `id` values in
  your dashboard.json5 `sources` array. Stale or missing values are replaced
  with the configured `stale_placeholder` (default: —).

  Example data object (from dashboard.example.json5):
    data.btc     → "42,350"   (or "—" if stale)
    data.weather → "12°C"     (or "—")
    data.power   → "2.4"      (or "—")
    data.clock   → "14:30"    (or "—")
-->
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <style>
    * { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }

    body {
      width: 296px;
      height: 128px;
      overflow: hidden;
      background: #ffffff;
      color: #000000;
      font-family: monospace;
      font-size: 11px;
    }

    /* ── Layout: two columns ───────────────────────────────────────────────── */
    .layout {
      display: flex;
      width: 296px;
      height: 128px;
    }

    /* Left column — BTC price (wide) */
    .col-left {
      width: 160px;
      border-right: 2px solid #000000;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
    }

    /* Right column — weather + power + clock */
    .col-right {
      width: 136px;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
    }

    /* ── Generic widget cell ───────────────────────────────────────────────── */
    .widget {
      flex: 1;
      padding: 4px 6px;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      justify-content: center;
      border-bottom: 1px solid #000000;
    }
    .widget:last-child { border-bottom: none; }

    .widget-label {
      font-size: 9px;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.05em;
      color: #000000;
      opacity: 0.6;
      line-height: 1;
    }

    .widget-value {
      font-size: 13px;
      font-weight: bold;
      line-height: 1.1;
      margin-top: 2px;
      white-space: nowrap;
      overflow: hidden;
      text-overflow: ellipsis;
    }

    /* ── BTC widget (occupies full left column) ─────────────────────────────── */
    .btc-widget {
      flex: 1;
      padding: 6px 8px;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      justify-content: center;
    }

    .btc-label {
      font-size: 10px;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.08em;
      color: #ff0000;
    }

    .btc-value {
      font-size: 28px;
      font-weight: bold;
      line-height: 1;
      letter-spacing: -0.02em;
      margin-top: 4px;
    }

    .btc-unit {
      font-size: 10px;
      color: #000000;
      margin-top: 2px;
    }

    /* ── Clock — red accent ────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
    .clock-widget {
      background: #000000;
      color: #ffffff;
    }

    .clock-widget .widget-label {
      color: #ffffff;
      opacity: 0.7;
    }

    .clock-widget .widget-value {
      font-size: 16px;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="layout">

    <!-- ── Left: BTC price ─────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <div class="col-left">
      <div class="btc-widget">
        <span class="btc-label">&#8383; Bitcoin</span>
        <span class="btc-value"><%= data.btc %></span>
        <span class="btc-unit">USD</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ── Right: weather / power / clock ─────────────────────────────────── -->
    <div class="col-right">

      <div class="widget">
        <span class="widget-label">Weather</span>
        <span class="widget-value"><%= data.weather %></span>
      </div>

      <div class="widget">
        <span class="widget-label">Power (kW)</span>
        <span class="widget-value"><%= data.power %></span>
      </div>

      <div class="widget clock-widget">
        <span class="widget-label">Time</span>
        <span class="widget-value"><%= data.clock %></span>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
